36:07.770 --> 36:10.470
Teller returned the card
to the deck and handed the deck

36:10.470 --> 36:12.370
to Lawrence to shuffle.

36:12.370 --> 36:15.430
Teller took the fully shuffled
cards back from the professor

36:15.430 --> 36:19.830
and took a quick look at
the random order of the faces.

36:19.830 --> 36:23.130
You know, every random order
contains some intrinsic

36:23.130 --> 36:24.600
qualities.

36:24.600 --> 36:28.700
The four aces always remind me
of the four fundamental

36:28.700 --> 36:30.530
interactions in nature.

36:30.530 --> 36:32.100
The Ace of Diamonds?

36:32.100 --> 36:35.330
That reminds me
of electromagnetism.

36:35.330 --> 36:38.870
And electromagnetism is a force
responsible for practically

36:38.870 --> 36:42.630
